== Dipping Sauce ==

Wash and dry produce. Drain @corn{1%unit}, then pat dry with #paper towels{}. Halve @orange{2%unit}; slice crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Thinly slice @mini cucumber{1%unit} into rounds.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @honey Dijon dressing{1.5%ounce}, @BBQ sauce{1%tablespoon}, and a pinch of @salt{}. (We sent more BBQ sauce; use any remaining as another dipper for fritters!)

== Corn Fritters ==

Roughly chop drained corn.

Add corn, @shredded cheddar{1/2%cup}, and @fry seasoning{1%tablespoon} to a #large bowl{}; stir to combine.

Stir in @tempura batter{82%g}, 1/3 cup cold water, ½ tsp salt, and @pepper{}. Batter should be very thick but not dry; add a splash of water if necessary.

Heat a 1/3-inch layer of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{}, preferably nonstick, over medium-high heat. Once oil is shimmering and hot enough that a drop of batter sizzles when added to the pan, carefully add heaping 1 1/2-TBSP scoops of batter to pan; press down lightly with a #spoon{}. Cook until golden brown and crisp, ~{3-4%minutes} per side.

Transfer fritters to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Season with salt.

== Assembly ==

To serve: Divide fritters between plates. Serve with dipping sauce, orange slices, cucumber, and @cheddar snack slices{3%unit} on the side.

To stash: Let fritters cool completely. Refrigerate fritters, dipping sauce, orange slices, and cucumber in separate #containers{} and pack with cheddar slices as desired!

== Chocolate Pudding ==

Combine @semisweet chocolate chips{3%ounce} and @cornstarch{1%tablespoon} in a second #large microwave-safe bowl{}; stir to coat. Add @milk{2%unit} and ¼ tsp salt; stir to combine.

Microwave, uncovered, until chocolate begins to melt, ~{1 1/2%minutes}. Gently whisk with a #whisk{} for ~{30%seconds}. Repeat microwaving and whisking 2-3 more times, until pudding begins to thicken and coats the back of a spoon.

> Keep a close eye on your bowl so it doesn't boil or overflow!

Carefully divide pudding between three #small serving bowls{} or containers. Place a layer of @plastic wrap{} on top, directly touching the pudding (this helps prevent a solid layer from forming on top!), then cover bowls with another layer of plastic wrap.

Chill in the #refrigerator{} for at least ~{1%hour} or up to overnight. Pudding will thicken as it cools. Serve straight from the bowls!

> It's natural for the pudding to begin to separate as it sits. Simply re-whisk before serving!